The paper deals with the problem of maximizing social influence in a network, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents an algorithmic solution to the problem, which involves graph algorithms and optimization techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the independent cascade model of network diffusion, which is a common model used in the study of social networks, making cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories as well.
